displayMetadata.flavor_description: Test your mettle in the Solo Cash Cup!

This tournament occurs across two rounds, with the top 600 players from Round 1 advancing to Round 2. Players must be at least 13 years old (or such other age, if greater, as may be required in their country of residence), have MFA enabled, have participated in at least 14 different tournaments within the last 180 days, and have an account level of 350 or greater. displayMetadata.flavor_description: Compete against other ranked players!

displayMetadata.flavor_description: Place into one of three weekly divisions in this seasonal kick off!

For EU, OCE, ASIA, ME, and BR - the top 1,400 teams at the end of Round 1 will advance to Round 2. The top 200 teams from Round 2 will be assigned to the Elite Division; the next 1000 teams will be assigned to the Challenger Division; and all other players will be assigned into the Contender Division. For NAE and NAW - the top 1,400 teams at the end of Round 1 will advance to Round 2. The top 100 teams from Round 2 will be assigned to the Elite Division; the next 500 teams will be assigned to the Challenger Division; and all other players will be assigned into the Contender Division. The Placement Cup will be region locked. The region you participate in for Placement Cup will be the same for all of Divisional Play. For more details see https://www.epicgames.com/fortnite/competitive/rules-library
